intro: Syzygium wenzelii, commonly known as the Wenzel's apple. It is a species of flowering plant in the family Myrtaceae, native to the rainforests of northeastern Queensland, Australia. The plant is characterized by its glossy, elliptical leaves and produces small, edible fruits that are typically red or yellow when ripe. Syzygium wenzelii thrives in humid, shaded environments and is often found in coastal and lowland rainforest areas. It plays an important ecological role by providing food for native wildlife and contributing to the biodiversity of its habitat.
